                            <comment id="17000054" author="beobal" created="Thu, 19 Dec 2019 13:13:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch abstracts the digest generation, wrapping the underlying &lt;tt&gt;Hasher&lt;/tt&gt; with a new &lt;tt&gt;Digest&lt;/tt&gt; class. Specializations of &lt;tt&gt;Digest&lt;/tt&gt; can incorporate logic depending on their specific usage; e.g. when generating a digest for repaired data tracking, don&apos;t include legacy counter shards. This also enables a lot of &lt;tt&gt;ByteBuffer&lt;/tt&gt; duplication to be removed.&lt;/p&gt;

