                            <comment id="17017042" author="krummas" created="Thu, 16 Jan 2020 15:42:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;few extremely minor nits that you can ignore or fix on commit:&lt;br/&gt;
 In &lt;tt&gt;Digest&lt;/tt&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;maybe use &lt;tt&gt;ThreadLocal.withInitial&lt;/tt&gt; for creating &lt;tt&gt;localBuffer&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;public Digest update(ByteBuffer input, int pos, int len)&lt;/tt&gt; can be private&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;update javadoc comment on &lt;tt&gt;public Digest updateWithCounterContext(ByteBuffer context)&lt;/tt&gt; (it is not &quot;&lt;tt&gt;updateDigest&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; anymore)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;UnfilteredPartitionIterators&lt;/tt&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;double indentation on &lt;tt&gt;UnfilteredRowIterators.digest(partition, digest, version);&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;public static void digest(...)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17021928" author="beobal" created="Thu, 23 Jan 2020 10:21:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, committed with nits addressed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
